RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 74. Allowance Purse 41000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOBNOBIN GENERAL trailed while along the inside into the far turn, angled four wide approaching the quarter pole, gained on the compact field into the lane, caught the leader near the eighth pole and quickly cleared. CORONA GRANDE raced near the inside through the turn when never far back, bid into the lane from the two path, split rivals late and was up for the place spot while not a threat to the top one. BRIGHT BRIAN set the pace along the inside into the turn, was put under pressure from multiple rivals through the turn and into the lane, was no match for the closing winner then grudgingly gave ground late to the place rival. JUANCHO stalked the pace from the three path through the turn, bid from the three or four path into the lane, was moving to the lead just outside the eighth pole when collared by the winner then weakened. FRUITCAKE was two wide through the turn when never far back, came into the lane from the four path and lacked a closing response. ROCK THE RED chased the pace from the two path through the turn then faded through the lane. OVERTHETOPJUSTICE was three wide through the turn when never far back then tired through the final eighth.
